  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Mild cognitive impairment (MCI) is accompanied by gait and balance problems while dual
      tasking. During a 6 to 8 weeks training with the BioRescue (virtual reality),
      institutionalized elderly people with MCI will relearn dual tasks in combination with
      balance. Afterwards, the transferring effect on gait in general, balance and cognition will
      be examined.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
